('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,87,89,'  Even as the tribes of thronging bees go forth from some hollow rock, ever coming on afresh, and in clusters over the flowers of spring fly in throngs, some here, some there;  even so from the ships and huts before the low sea-beach marched forth in companies their many tribes to the place of gathering.'),
