('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,147,149,' And even as when the West Wind at its coming stirreth a deep cornfield with its violent blast, and the ears bow thereunder, even so was all their gathering stirred, and they with loud shouting rushed towards the ships;  and from beneath their feet the dust arose on high.'),
