('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,195,195,'  Did we not all hear what he spake in the council?'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,196,197,'  Beware lest waxing wroth he work mischief to the sons of the Achaeans. Proud is the heart of kings, fostered of heaven; for their honour is from Zeus, and Zeus, god of counsel, loveth them.\"'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,198,199,'\nBut whatsoever man of the people he saw, and found brawling, him would he smite with his staff; and chide with words, saying,  \"Fellow, sit thou still, and hearken to the words of others that are better men than thou; whereas thou art unwarlike and a weakling, neither to be counted in war nor in counsel.'),
