('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,207,210,'\nThus masterfully did he range through the host, and they hasted back to the place of gathering from their ships and huts with noise, as when a wave of the loud-resounding sea  thundereth on the long beach, and the deep roareth.\nNow the others sate them down and were stayed in their places, only there still kept chattering on Thersites of measureless speech, whose mind was full of great store of disorderly words, wherewith to utter revilings against the kings, idly, and in no orderly wise,  but whatsoever he deemed would raise a laugh among the Argives.'),
