('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,350,353,'  For I declare that Cronos\' son, supreme in might, gave promise with his nod on that day when the Argives went on board their swift-faring ships, bearing unto the Trojans death and fate; for he lightened on our right and shewed forth signs of good.  Wherefore let no man make haste to depart homewards until each have lain with the wife of some Trojan,  and have got him requital for his strivings and groanings for Helen\'s sake.'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,354,356,'  For I declare that Cronos\' son, supreme in might, gave promise with his nod on that day when the Argives went on board their swift-faring ships, bearing unto the Trojans death and fate; for he lightened on our right and shewed forth signs of good.  Wherefore let no man make haste to depart homewards until each have lain with the wife of some Trojan,  and have got him requital for his strivings and groanings for Helen\'s sake.'),
