('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,371,372,'  \"Aye verily once more, old sir, art thou pre-eminent in speech above the sons of the Achaeans. I would, O father Zeus and Athene and Apollo, that I had ten such counsellors; then would the city of king Priam forthwith bow her head, taken and laid waste beneath our hands.'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,373,374,'  \"Aye verily once more, old sir, art thou pre-eminent in speech above the sons of the Achaeans. I would, O father Zeus and Athene and Apollo, that I had ten such counsellors; then would the city of king Priam forthwith bow her head, taken and laid waste beneath our hands.'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,375,376,'  But the son of Cronos, even Zeus that beareth the aegis, hath brought sorrows upon me, in that he casteth me into the midst of fruitless strifes and wranglings.'),
