('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,524,524,'  With these followed forty black ships.'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,525,526,'  And their leaders busily marshalled the ranks of the Phocians, and made ready for battle hard by the Boeotians on the left.'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,527,529,'\nAnd the Loerians had as leader the swift son of Oïleus, Aias the less, in no wise as great as Telamonian Aias, but far less.'),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,529,530,'  Small of stature was he, with corselet of linen,  but with the spear he far excelled the whole host of Hellenes and Achaeans. These were they that dwelt in Cynus and Opus and Calliarus and Bessa and Scarphe and lovely Augeiae and Tarphe and Thronium about the streams of Boagrius.'),
