('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,578,580,'  With him followed most people by far and goodliest; and among them he himself did on his gleaming bronze, a king all-glorious, and was pre-eminent among all the warriors, '),
('urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1',2,581,587,' \nAnd they that held the hollow land of Lacedaemon with its many ravines, and Pharis and Sparta and Messe, the haunt of doves, and that dwelt in Bryseiae and lovely Augeiae, and that held Amyclae and Helus, a citadel hard by the sea,  and that held Laas, and dwelt about Oetylus,—these were led by Agamemnon\'s brother, even Menelaus, good at the war-cry, with sixty ships; and they were marshalled apart.'),
